5:["$","article",null,{"className":"mx-auto flex max-w-2xl flex-col px-6 py-16","children":[["$","script",null,{"type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"[{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"Article\",\"headline\":\"SEO you can't forget to do: how we made GEO a build gate\",\"url\":\"http://blog.stack.localhost:1355/seo-as-a-build-gate\",\"mainEntityOfPage\":\"http://blog.stack.localhost:1355/seo-as-a-build-gate\",\"description\":\"We turned Google's AI-optimization advice into a script that fails the build. Here's what check:seo actually enforces — and the honest part it can't: original, first-hand content.\",\"datePublished\":\"2026-07-01\",\"dateModified\":\"2026-07-02\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Person\",\"name\":\"The builders-stack team\"}},{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"BreadcrumbList\",\"itemListElement\":[{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":1,\"name\":\"Blog\",\"item\":\"http://blog.stack.localhost:1355/\"},{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":2,\"name\":\"SEO you can't forget to do: how we made GEO a build gate\",\"item\":\"http://blog.stack.localhost:1355/seo-as-a-build-gate\"}]}]"}}],["$","$L10",null,{"href":"/","className":"mb-8 text-sm text-muted-foreground hover:text-foreground","children":"← All posts"}],["$","header",null,{"className":"mb-8 flex flex-col gap-4","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2 text-sm text-muted-foreground","children":[["$","time",null,{"dateTime":"2026-07-01","children":"July 1, 2026"}],["$","span",null,{"aria-hidden":true,"children":"·"}],["$","span",null,{"children":"The builders-stack team"}],[["$","span",null,{"aria-hidden":true,"children":"·"}],["$","span",null,{"children":["Updated ","July 2, 2026"]}]]]}],["$","h1",null,{"className":"text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight","children":"SEO you can't forget to do: how we made GEO a build gate"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-lg text-muted-foreground","children":"We turned Google's AI-optimization advice into a script that fails the build. Here's what check:seo actually enforces — and the honest part it can't: original, first-hand content."}],["$","div",null,{"className":"flex flex-wrap gap-2","children":[["$","span","seo",{"data-slot":"badge","className":"inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-1 rounded-md border px-2 py-0.5 text-xs font-medium w-fit whitespace-nowrap shrink-0 transition-colors overflow-hidden [&>svg]:size-3 [&>svg]:pointer-events-none focus-visible:border-ring focus-visible:ring-ring/50 focus-visible:ring-[3px] aria-invalid:border-destructive aria-invalid:ring-destructive/20 border-transparent bg-secondary text-secondary-foreground","children":"seo"}],["$","span","geo",{"data-slot":"badge","className":"inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-1 rounded-md border px-2 py-0.5 text-xs font-medium w-fit whitespace-nowrap shrink-0 transition-colors overflow-hidden [&>svg]:size-3 [&>svg]:pointer-events-none focus-visible:border-ring focus-visible:ring-ring/50 focus-visible:ring-[3px] aria-invalid:border-destructive aria-invalid:ring-destructive/20 border-transparent bg-secondary text-secondary-foreground","children":"geo"}],["$","span","structure",{"data-slot":"badge","className":"inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-1 rounded-md border px-2 py-0.5 text-xs font-medium w-fit whitespace-nowrap shrink-0 transition-colors overflow-hidden [&>svg]:size-3 [&>svg]:pointer-events-none focus-visible:border-ring focus-visible:ring-ring/50 focus-visible:ring-[3px] aria-invalid:border-destructive aria-invalid:ring-destructive/20 border-transparent bg-secondary text-secondary-foreground","children":"structure"}]]}]]}],"$L11"]}]
11:["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","p",null,{"className":"my-4 leading-7 text-foreground/90","children":["Every team says SEO matters and then ships a page with no ",["$","code",null,{"className":"rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm","children":"<title>"}],", no canonical, and a\nclient-only shell that renders nothing until JavaScript runs. Not out of malice — it\njust isn't anyone's job on the day the page ships. So in builders-stack we did the only\nthing that reliably changes behavior: we made the omission fail ",["$","code",null,{"className":"rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm","children":"bun run check"}],". This\npost is the honest version of what that gate does, and the bigger thing it deliberately\ndoes not."]}],"\n",["$","h2",null,{"className":"mt-12 mb-4 text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight","children":"What a script can enforce"}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"className":"my-4 leading-7 text-foreground/90","children":[["$","code",null,{"className":"rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm","children":"scripts/check-seo.ts"}]," walks every public ",["$","code",null,{"className":"rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm","children":"page.tsx"}]," across all apps and refuses to pass\nif any of three things is missing. The rules come straight from\n",["$","a",null,{"className":"font-medium text-primary underline underline-offset-4","href":"https://developers.google.com/search/docs/fundamentals/ai-optimization-guide","children":"Google's AI optimization guide"}],":"]}],"\n",["$","ul",null,{"className":"my-4 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6 text-foreground/90","children":["\n",["$","li",null,{"className":"leading-7","children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"The page is indexable with a snippet"}]," — it must export ",["$","code",null,{"className":"rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm","children":"metadata"}]," or\n",["$","code",null,{"className":"rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm","children":"generateMetadata"}],". In practice that means it goes through ",["$","code",null,{"className":"rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm","children":"@stack/seo"}],"'s\n",["$","code",null,{"className":"rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm","children":"pageMetadata()"}],", the one door that fills canonical, Open Graph, and Twitter cards from\na single config so no page hand-rolls them and drifts."]}],"\n",["$","li",null,{"className":"leading-7","children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"The content is server-rendered"}]," — a public page can't be a root ",["$","code",null,{"className":"rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm","children":"\"use client\""}],"\ncomponent. If a crawler (or an AI answer engine) gets an empty div, you don't exist.\nInteractivity is allowed; it just has to live in a child component."]}],"\n",["$","li",null,{"className":"leading-7","children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"The site is discoverable"}]," — every app serving public pages needs ",["$","code",null,{"className":"rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm","children":"robots.ts"}]," and\n",["$","code",null,{"className":"rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm","children":"sitemap.ts"}],". The blog's sitemap is generated from the content directory, so a new\npost can't be left out of it."]}],"\n"]}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"className":"my-4 leading-7 text-foreground/90","children":["Because the check is wired into ",["$","code",null,{"className":"rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm","children":"bun run check"}],", the lefthook pre-push hook, and CI,\nthere is no path to ",["$","code",null,{"className":"rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm","children":"main"}]," that skips it. The structured data (",["$","code",null,{"className":"rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm","children":"articleJsonLd"}]," +\n","$L12",") that earns rich results is built the same way — from ","$L13",", never a\nhand-inlined ","$L14"," tag that goes stale."]}],"\n","$L15","\n","$L16","\n","$L17","\n","$L18","\n","$L19","\n","$L1a"]}]
